OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,420,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1776985387
OL,3,CMan sentenced for making over 200
OL,4,Cabusive 999 calls
OL,6,FHe averaged at over one call a day
OL,7,Fover a seven month period, with
OL,8,Fparticular highs in October and
OL,9,FDecember when he made nearly 50 calls
OL,10,Feach month.
OL,12,FMurphy, of Salt Marsh Road in
OL,13,FShoreham, was linked to the calls and
OL,14,Fhe was arrested on 19 January.
OL,16,FHe was charged the same day with
OL,17,Fpersistently making use of a public
OL,18,Fcommunication network to cause
OL,19,Fannoyance/ inconvenience/ anxiety.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,420,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1776985387
OL,3,CMan sentenced for making over 200
OL,4,Cabusive 999 calls
OL,6,FAfter being conditional bailed, Murphy
OL,7,Fcontinued to contact police regularly,
OL,8,Fmaking nearly 70 calls between January
OL,9,Fand February.
OL,11,FHe appeared at Worthing Magistrates'
OL,12,FCourt on 3 March to answer the charges
OL,13,Fand went on to plead not guilty.
OL,15,FFollowing a further hearing at
OL,16,FWorthing Magistrates' Court on 14
OL,17,FApril, Murphy changed his plea to
OL,18,Fguilty and was sentenced the same day.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,420,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1776985387
OL,3,CMan sentenced for making over 200
OL,4,Cabusive 999 calls
OL,6,FHe received a two year Criminal
OL,7,FBehaviour Order (CBO), prohibiting him
OL,8,Ffrom calling any emergency phone
OL,9,Fnumber unless there is a genuine need.
OL,11,FLeading the investigation, Laura
OL,12,FHerbert-Price, said; "Over 200 calls
OL,13,Fwere made to police, all either
OL,14,Fabusive or entirely fabricated,
OL,15,Fresulting in considerable time and
OL,16,Fresources spent both dealing with
OL,17,FMurphy, and in preparing material for
OL,18,Fthe Crown Prosecution Service.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,420,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1776985387
OL,3,CMan sentenced for making over 200
OL,4,Cabusive 999 calls
OL,6,F"This behaviour cannot be tolerated
OL,7,Fand directly impacts our ability to
OL,8,Frespond to those genuinely in need of
OL,9,Fcritical services.
OL,11,F"Following tireless efforts, the
OL,12,Fcourts have now issued Murphy with a
OL,13,FCriminal Behaviour Order, ensuring he
OL,14,Fis held accountable for his actions."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
